    schema:activitiesWorkload "100%"@es ;
    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000024/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description """Though biology has quicky become a data-centric science, the practitioners of biology have not understood the importance of their data - in particular, the care that must be taken in annotating it, describing and representing it, and publishing it. Therefore, the greatest challenge for bioinformaticians at this time is related to Finding data, Accessing data, Integrating data, and Reusing data (F.A.I.R.). This course will initially focus on problems related to large-scale data integration. We will study the software tools for capturing data, from files and then directly from the Web. We will learn to manipulate data structures, and how to write clear software that represents complex data structures. We will learn about contemporary approaches to data and knowledge modeling in the life sciences. We will learn how to use these contemporary approaches to do global-scale, cross-resource queries, such that we can integrate the massive amounts of data our biologist colleagues require to interpret their results. Finally, we will learn how to publish scholarly data in a FAIR manner, and how to create Web interfaces to make these massive integrated datasets tractable for biologists.
This course is aimed at students who are already competent programmers, generally with several years of experience, who want to challenge their skills with a wide range of real-world, complex biological informatics coding and data exploration tasks. Students who do not have significant prior experience in coding should not consider this course - for students with insufficient coding skills, this course will be frustratingly time-consuming and interfere with your success in other courses. Assignments are provided approximately every 2 weeks, and have a 2 or 3 week submission deadline (depending on the complexity of the task). These deadlines are firm and will not be extended."""@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/mark.wilkinson%40upm.es> ;
    schema:inLanguage "Castellano"@es ;
    schema:instructor <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/mark.wilkinson%40upm.es> ;
    schema:name "Retos en Programación Informática"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000024/2025-26/CE01> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE01" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Comprender las bases moleculares y las técnicas experimentales estándares más comunes en las investigaciones ómicas (genómica, transcriptómica, proteómica, metabolómica, interactómica, etc.)/ Understanding the molecular basis and standard experimental techniques in ?omics research (genomics, transcriptomics, proteomics, interactomics, etc)."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000024/2025-26/CE04> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE04" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Utilizar diferentes bases de datos (incluidos los bigdata), conocer sus estructuras y ontologías, aplicar la estadística a su análisis, siendo capaz de utilizar herramientas de representación y visualización/ Utilizing different databases (including those for bigdata), knowing their structures and ontologies, applying statistical analyses, and using tools for their representation and visualization."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000024/2025-26/CE08> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE08" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad de integrar tecnologías y sistemas propios de la Inteligencia Artificial, con carácter generalista, y en contextos más amplios y multidisciplinares/ Acquire the capacity of integrating Artificial Intelligence technologies and systems in broader and multidisciplinar contexts."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000024/2025-26/CE09> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CE09" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad de interpretar los modelos de clasificación supervisada y no supervisada obtenidos al aplicar las técnicas de Aprendizaje Automático para un conjunto de datos/ Acquire the capacity of interpreting supervised and unsupervised classification methods obtained when applying Machine Learning methods to datasets."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000024/2025-26/CG02> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG02" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Familiarizarse con el trabajo y los métodos de la Biología Computacional en condiciones reales, adquiriendo la capacidad de diseñar aplicaciones/experimentos de forma independiente y describir, cuantificar, analizar y evaluar críticamente los resultados obtenidos/ Becoming familiar with the work and methods in Computational Biology in real situations, acquiring the capacity of design applications/experiments in an independent manner and critically describe, quantify, analyze and evaluate the obtained results."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000024/2025-26/CG05> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CG05" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Que los estudiantes sean capaces de integrar conocimientos en el area de la Biología Computacional, de formular conclusiones, hipótesis o líneas de trabajo a partir de la información disponible, y de formarse una opinion fundamentada sobre las responsabilidades sociales y éticas vinculadas a la aplicación de sus conocimientos/ Provide students with the capacity to integrate knowledge in the area of Computational Biology, formulate conclusions, hypotheses or research lines from the available information, and with the ability to elaborate solid opinions about the social and ethic responsibilities derived from the application of their knowledge."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000024/2025-26/CT02> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT02" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Capacidad para aplicar el método científico para la resolución de problemas de forma efectiva y creativa/ Capacity to apply the scientific method to solve problems in an efective and creative way."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000024/2025-26/CT03> a ns1:Competency ;
    ns1:competencyCode "CT03" ;
    ns1:competencyDescription "Tener compromiso bioético y profesional y respeto por la sostenibilidad ambiental/ To have bioethics and professional awareness for environmental sustainability."@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000024/2025-26/RA7> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA7" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Adquirir conocimientos para el manejo de técnicas avanzadas de representación de datos y enfoques de integración masiva de datos"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000024/2025-26/RA8> a ns1:LearningResult ;
    ns1:learningResultCode "RA8" ;
    ns1:learningResultDescription "Adquisición de conocimientos de cuales son las mejores prácticas para la publicación de datos científicos"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/203000024/2025-26/RA9> a ns1:LearningResult ;
